# Purpose

Enforce backend-specific coding conventions. Universal TypeScript rules are in `global/coding-standards.mdc`.

# Rules

## Naming

- All source files: `kebab-case.ts` (e.g. `auth-controller.ts`, `job-pipeline.ts`).
- No `.tsx` files in the backend.

## Imports

- Path alias: `*` maps to `src/*` (configured in `tsconfig.json`).
- Import internal modules without a path prefix: `import config from 'config'`, `import constants from 'shared/constants'`.
- DO NOT use relative `../../` imports when a path alias resolves the target.

## Validation

- Validate all request bodies in middleware before the controller runs.
- Use `validateRequestPayload(schema, req.body, ErrorMessage.X)` in domain middleware.
- Use `parseSchema(schema, data)` from `lib/validation` for safe parsing inside repositories and services.
- Both functions return `SchemaResult<T>` — check `result.success` before using `result.data`.

## Error Handling

- Throw typed exceptions from `aop/exceptions`. DO NOT call `res.status().json()` for errors in controllers.

| Exception | When to use |
|---|---|
| `UnauthorizedException` | User identity check failed |
| `TokenException` | JWT invalid or missing |
| `ConflictException` | Duplicate key (MongoDB 11000) |
| `ResourceNotFoundException` | Document not found |
| `BusinessLogicException` | Domain rule violation |
| `InputValidationException` | Request body fails schema |
| `SchemaValidationException` | DB document fails schema |
| `DatabaseException` | Unclassified MongoDB error |
| `InternalException` | Unexpected / unhandled error |

- `exceptionsMiddleware` catches all thrown exceptions and serializes them.
- Re-throw errors inside transaction `catch` blocks after calling `abortTransaction`.

## Logging

- Import `logger` from `aop/logging`.
- Use `logger.error(message, { error })`, `logger.warn(message)`, `logger.info(message)`.
- DO NOT use `console.log` / `console.error` in production code paths.

# Anti-Patterns

```typescript
// ❌ Manual error response in controller
res.status(400).json({ success: false, message: 'Not found' });

// ✅ Throw typed exception
throw new ResourceNotFoundException(ErrorMessage.JOB_NOT_FOUND);

// ❌ console in production path
console.log('user created');

// ✅ Structured logger
logger.info('User created', { userId });

// ❌ Relative import when alias resolves it
import config from '../../../config';

// ✅ Path alias
import config from 'config';
```

# Checklist

- [ ] All files named `kebab-case.ts`
- [ ] Internal imports use path aliases, not `../../`
- [ ] Request body validated in middleware before controller
- [ ] Typed exception thrown (not manual `res.status().json()`)
- [ ] `logger` used, not `console`
